## Decision 3 — W1A: V3 module-hash interim

**Design (CC).** `mktd02::init` / `on_post_upgrade` wired with an additive `mktd_module_hash: Option<[u8;32]>`.
`None → [0u8;32]` does **not** satisfy V3. Full V3 needs the installer (`local_user_index`) to supply the
real module hash at install/upgrade — out of P1 scope. Interim: two-pass attestation.

**Impact.** Until the installer wiring lands, OpenChatZD receipts are effectively **V1–V2 (+ V3 pending)**,
not the D3 V1–V3 profile. That must be disclosed in the receipt / verification copy.

**Asked of G:** confirm the placeholder + deferred full-V3 (installer-supplied module hash) is acceptable
for P1, with V3-pending disclosed; confirm full V3 lands in a named follow-up packet.

